{{Quote|To state our allegations, I present Queen Amidala, recently elected ruler of Naboo, who speaks on our behalf.|Senator [[Darth Sidious|Palpatine]], to the [[Galactic Senate]]|<ref name="Episode I" />}}
The '''Monarch of Naboo''' was the [[Democracy|elected]] monarch, such as a [[king]] or [[queen]], of the [[Royal House of Naboo]], the [[monarchy]] that governed the [[human]] [[Naboo (people)|denizens]] of [[Naboo|the planet]].

==Description==
The Monarch of Naboo was an [[Democracy|elected]] monarch who stood as the leader of the [[Royal House of Naboo]], governing the [[human]] [[Naboo (people)|population]] of the [[planet]] [[Naboo]].<ref name="Episode I" /> They served for two-[[Standard year|year]] terms which were renewable once.<ref name="Queen's Shadow">''[[Queen's Shadow]]''</ref> The people of Naboo often elected young [[Gender|women]], believing they possessed a form of pure, childlike wisdom that the adults lacked.<ref name="SW:AEYNtK">''[[Star Wars: Absolutely Everything You Need to Know]]''</ref> Theoretically, however, virtually anyone could be elected the new king or queen.<ref name="The Star Wars Book">''[[The Star Wars Book]]''</ref> Due to tradition and to protect their loved ones, Naboo monarchs adopted new identities when they began to campaign for the position, changing at least their last name. Even so, some monarchs proved to be less protective of their anonymity than others. They could return to their previous identity after their term ended<ref name="Queen's Peril">''[[Queen's Peril]]''</ref> or chose to retain<ref name="Episode II" /> their new name.<ref name="Queen's Peril" /> The monarch was aided by the [[Naboo Royal Advisory Council]].<ref name="NeeyutneeDB" /> The proper form of address for a former queen of Naboo was "M'Lady."<ref name="Complete Vehicles 2018">[[Star Wars: Complete Vehicles (2018)|''Star Wars: Complete Vehicles'' (2018)]]</ref>

==History==
===Republic Era===
Around [[382 BBY]],<ref name="382 Date">''[[Star Wars: The High Republic Character Encyclopedia]]'' dates the events of ''[[The High Republic: Convergence]]'' to [[382 BBY]].</ref> a [[Unidentified Queen of Naboo (382 BBY)|queen]] served as the monarch of Naboo. That queen owned a [[Unidentified Queen of Naboo's yacht|yacht]], which the [[gambler]] [[Axel Greylark]] wanted to buy with his inheritance.<ref name="Convergence">''[[The High Republic: Convergence]]''</ref> Queens of Naboo included [[Padmé Amidala]], who served two terms,<ref name="Episode II" /> the first of which included the [[Invasion of Naboo]];<ref name="Episode I" /> Amidala's predecessor Queen [[Sanandrassa]],<ref name="Queen's Shadow" /> who was herself preceded by [[Réillata]], who served one term<ref name="Queen's Peril" /> before successfully running again to serve a second term after Amidala's tenure;<ref name="Queen's Shadow" /> [[Jamillia]], who served shortly before the [[First Battle of Geonosis|outbreak]] of the [[Clone Wars]];<ref name="Episode II" /> [[Neeyutnee]], who served during the war;<ref name="Blue Shadow Virus">{{TCW|Blue Shadow Virus (episode)}}</ref> and [[Apailana]], who served during the early [[Standard day|days]] of the [[Galactic Empire]].<ref name="Episode III">{{Film|III}}</ref> During the Invasion of Naboo, [[Viceroy of the Trade Federation]] [[Nute Gunray]] claimed the throne<ref name="SWESioBibble" /> until he was overthrown by Amidala in the [[Battle of Naboo]].<ref name="Episode I" />

===Imperial Era===
Whilst the position of monarch carried with it actual power and an active role in governing the planet and its people, the establishment of the Galactic Empire saw the position reduced to that of a mere figurehead as all meaningful authority was transferred to the newly appointed [[Moff]] [[Quarsh Panaka]].<ref name="Princess of Alderaan" /> In the process, the Empire supplanted the authority of the planet's monarch.<ref name="Legacy4" /> Queen [[Dalné]], who served around [[3 BBY]]<ref name="Dalné Date">''[[Star Wars: Timelines]]'' dates the events of ''[[Leia, Princess of Alderaan]]'' to [[3 BBY]].</ref> and was heavily resentful of her reduced authority, nevertheless reluctantly went along with it rather than challenge the Empire and risk Imperial retribution for defiance.<ref name="Princess of Alderaan" />

Naboo continued to prosper under the Empire and did not suffer, even if its citizens knew their safety and wealth depended on accepting the loss of their freedoms. Nonetheless, Naboo did experience a moment of Imperial punishment when the [[Sith Lord]] [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]]&mdash;secretly the former Jedi [[Anakin Skywalker]] and husband of the deceased Amidala&mdash;descended upon Naboo, seemingly embarking on a crusade to wipe away all memory of his dead wife. Vader cut down anyone who dared reference her memory, although her legacy as a beloved queen would survive his rampage.<ref name="Legacy4" /> [[Sosha Soruna]] served as queen around the [[time]] following the [[Battle of Endor]].<ref name="SE 2">[[Shattered Empire 2|''Shattered Empire'' 2]]</ref>

===New Republic Era and beyond===
{{Quote|People of Naboo. This is the Supreme Leader of the First Order. I have commandeered your communications network. I am unimpressed with you. Your focus on events that happened ''decades'' ago, your obsession with linage and superstition&hellip;have caused your society to fester. Because you cannot let go&hellip;you hold yourself back. Now that will change. All that was will be swept away. Naboo will embrace the future. You have been ruled by queens. You have been ruled by an emperor. Now&hellip; ''I am your king.''|Kylo Ren declares himself monarch|<ref name="Legacy4" />}}
In the wake of the Empire's fall, some people across the galaxy&mdash;having already been well aware of the fact that Naboo did not suffer under Imperial rule&mdash;felt that the planet should be punished, accusing certain citizens of profiting from the Empire.<ref name="Legacy4" /> Even though Soruna and others on Naboo regarded Palpatine with distain,<ref name="SE 2">[[Shattered Empire 2|''Shattered Empire'' 2]]</ref> the [[Verunas]], one of the former ruling families of Naboo, did profit greatly under Imperial rule. As new factions arose and distrust spread, Naboo's galactic influence was destroyed. All the while, the Verunas began annexing territory across Naboo and charging rent for its people to continue living there, securing a new source of income and killing those who rejected their authority.<ref name="Legacy4" />

In [[34 ABY]],<ref name="34Date">{{YouTube|video=0Mp3MNsQVDQ|text=The FUTURE of Star Wars Comics - An Interview With Charles Soule, Marc Guggenheim, and Alex Segura|channel=@StarWarsExplained|name=Star Wars Explained}} establishes that the events of ''[[Star Wars: Legacy of Vader]]'' take place immediately after the events of {{Film|VIII}}, which takes place in [[34 ABY]] per ''[[Star Wars: Timelines]]''.</ref> [[Supreme Leader]] [[Ben Solo|Kylo Ren]], the grandson of Vader and Amidala, ventured to Naboo to continue his study into his grandfather's background with Vader's former servant, [[Vaneé]]. While on world, Vaneé told Ren of the monarchy and Naboo's fall from grace, all while trying to make the Supreme Leader view the past as a fuel from which he could gather strength. Ren, however, regarded the past as a weakness and&mdash;unimpressed with how Naboo held so tightly onto the memory of its glory days&mdash;ordered a [[Assault on Naboo (First Order)|First Order attack on Naboo]], declaring himself the new King of Naboo in the process. Ren declared to the people of Naboo that, under his rule, they would have no choice but to embrace the future instead of remaining stagnant.<ref name="Legacy4" />

