==Behind the scenes==
The title of Monarch of Naboo first appeared in the [[1999]] film [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']].<ref name="Episode I" />

The [[2016]] reference book ''[[Star Wars Character Encyclopedia: Updated and Expanded]]'' states that [[King]] [[Ars Veruna]] preceded [[Padmé Amidala]] as monarch of Naboo,<ref name="SWEUE">''[[Star Wars Character Encyclopedia: Updated and Expanded]]''</ref> with [[Star Wars: Complete Locations (2016)|''Star Wars: Complete Locations'' (2016)]] adding that he ruled for 13 [[Standard year|years]].<ref name="SWCL">[[Star Wars: Complete Locations (2016)|''Star Wars: Complete Locations'']]</ref> The novel [[Tarkin (novel)|''Tarkin'']] (2014) previously stated that Naboo was ruled by a king fifteen years before the rise of the [[Galactic Empire]],<ref name="Tarkin">[[Tarkin (novel)|''Tarkin'']]</ref> which would correspond to [[34 BBY]],<ref name="Tarkin date">''[[Star Wars: Timelines]]'' dates the events of [[Tarkin (novel)|''Tarkin'']] to [[14 BBY]]. The flashback takes place twenty years prior to the main narrative, which can be calculated to [[34 BBY]].</ref> and the the [[Star Wars Helmet Collection 54|fifty-fourth]] issue of the magazine ''[[Star Wars Helmet Collection]]'' (2018) also lists him as monarch before being assassinated.<ref name="HC 54">{{HelmetCollectionCite|54|Weapons & Uniforms}}</ref> However, the novel ''[[Queen's Shadow]]'' (2019) states that monarchs are limited to two two-year terms,<ref name="Queen's Shadow" /> and its prequel ''[[Queen's Peril]]'' (2020) instead names Amidala's predecessors as Queens [[Sanandrassa]] and [[Réillata]], who both served for one term,<ref name="Queen's Peril" /> placing their reigns in 34 [['ABY-BBY' dating system|BBY]]<ref name="Timelines" /> giving no room for the king mentioned in ''Tarkin''.

The later editions of the ''Character Encyclopedia'' and ''Complete Locations'', ''[[Star Wars: Character Encyclopedia, Updated and Expanded Edition]]'' and ''[[Star Wars: Complete Locations, New Edition]]'' remove the mentions of Veruna.<ref name="SWCEUEE">''[[Star Wars: Character Encyclopedia, Updated and Expanded Edition]]''</ref><ref name="CLNE">''[[Star Wars: Complete Locations, New Edition]]''</ref> [[King/Legends|King]] [[Ars Veruna/Legends|Ars Veruna]] originally served as the monarchs of Naboo for 13 years in [[Star Wars Legends|Legends]] before being murdered by [[Darth Plagueis/Legends|Darth Plagueis]].<ref name="Darth Plagueis">[[Darth Plagueis (novel)|''Darth Plagueis'']]</ref>

"[[Database]]," a department in the 2019 magazine [[Star Wars - Das offizielle Magazin 96|''Star Wars - Das offizielle Magazin'' 96]], provides a different order for the Monarchs of Naboo. It mistakenly states that [[Ekay]] came after Réillata,<ref name="Magazine">{{GermanFanCite|96|Database}}</ref> when Ekay actually came before.<ref name="Timelines" /> It also places Veruna after Ekay, and maintains that he was Amidala's predecessor.<ref name="Magazine" /> It does not mention [[Ameé]] or Sanandrassa, as the magazine predates these characters.

''Queen's Shadow'' (2019) established that monarchs of Naboo serve for two-year terms.<ref name="Queen's Shadow" /> However, "[[Naboo (reference book)|Naboo]]," a 2020 issue of the French [[Star Wars Encyclopedia (series)|''Star Wars Encyclopedia'']], states that a term was four years<ref name="Altaya">{{EncyclopediaCite|Naboo}}</ref> as was the case in Legends. This article assumes that the previously defined term length of two years is correct.

